        dc:description           "FIG. 4. — A, B, Coralliophila erosa (Röding, 1798), Banc Président Thiers, BENTHAUS, stn DW 1926, 24°38.2’S, 146°00.8’W, 50- 90 m; C, D, C. monodonta (Blainville, 1832), Banc Arago, BENTHAUS, stn DW 1984, 23°26.4’S, 150°43.9’W, 40 m; E-I, C. fimbriata (A. Adams, 1854); E, F, North of Raivavae Is., BENTHAUS, stn DW 1939, 23°49.7’S, 147°41.6’W, 100 m, (detached from the original coral); G-I, Rimatara Is., BENTHAUS stn DW 2013, 22°38.6’S, 152°49.7’W, 80-93 m, 17 dd (arrows point to the mark on the coral skeleton). Scale bars: A-F, H, 10 mm; G, 30 mm; I, 5 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4520196/files/figure.png" .

